{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_ynIVCQem7L99hNZtqnm4S7Qz","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## Summary\n\nI have successfully reviewed and updated the PRD for **TST-001: FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement** based on the provided analyst answers. Here are the changes made:\n\n### Files Updated\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md`\n\n### Key Updates Made\n\n1. **Status**: Already set to `READY` (all required fields complete)\n\n2. **Section 1. Обзор (Overview)**:\n   - Product name: FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n   - Date/version: 2026-03-18 v1\n   - Brief description of the initiative\n\n3. **Section 2. Контекст и проблемы**:\n   - Current situation: Custom JWT-claims middleware exists but lacks live enforcement\n   - Problems: Security gaps, stale permissions, missing audit trail, unlogged 403s\n\n4. **Section 3. Цели и метрики успеха**:\n   - North Star: 100% mutation APIs protected\n   - Supporting metrics: P95 ≤ 10ms, sync ≤ 5s, 100% audit coverage\n\n5. **Section 5. Пользовательские сценарии**:\n   - Added 3 detailed scenarios covering admin role changes, 403 handling, and live sync\n\n6. **Section 6. Требования**:\n   - Functional: RBAC for POST/PUT/DELETE, audit logging, WebSocket push\n   - Non-functional: Latency, stability, retention policy, graceful degradation\n   - AC-1 through AC-4 defined\n\n7. **Section 7-10**: Updated constraints, plan, risks (with table), and closed questions\n\n8. **AIDD:RESEARCH_HINTS** - Enhanced with specific paths and detailed research notes:\n   - Paths: `src/middleware:src/auth:src/routes:frontend/src/guards:frontend/src/store:frontend/src/context:src/models:src/db/migrations`\n   - Keywords: Expanded list including `roleGuard, requireRole, checkPermission, websocket, socket, grant, revoke`\n   - 7 specific research tasks for the researcher stage\n\n9. **AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS**: Set to `none` (all answered)\n10. **AIDD:DECISIONS**: All 5 questions (Q1-Q5) documented with answers\n\n### Synthesis of Analyst Answers\n| Question | Answer | Impact on PRD |\n|----------|--------|---------------|\n| Q1 | B (All mutation APIs) | Scope covers POST/PUT/DELETE endpoints |\n| Q2 | B (Custom JWT middleware) | Extend existing middleware, not replace |\n| Q3 | A (React + Context/Redux) | Frontend integration uses Redux state |\n| Q4 | A (Database table) | Audit logs stored in DB with retention |\n| Q5 | A (WebSocket push) | Real-time sync via WebSocket |"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aed16250849e8891b (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 31437\ntool_uses: 23\nduration_ms: 292917</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8bf45a30-ee14-4cd7-b180-00fa1c43e905","uuid":"fa578e22-c0e6-4cee-af35-0eccd5aadb4b","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"You are the analyst for TST-001: FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement.\n\n## Your Task\nRead the rolling context pack at `aidd/reports/context/TST-001.pack.md` and the PRD at `aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md`. \n\nThe user has already provided answers to all analyst questions:\n- Q1=B: All mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) require RBAC control\n- Q2=B: Current implementation is custom middleware on JWT-claims\n- Q3=A: Frontend uses React + Context/Redux\n- Q4=A: Audit logs go to database (separate table)\n- Q5=A: Session sync uses WebSocket (push updates)\n\n## Your Output\n1. Review the PRD sections and update/improve based on the answers\n2. Fill in sections that reference the answers (Overview, Context, Goals, etc.)\n3. Ensure the PRD is consistent with the analyst responses\n4. Update the AIDD:RESEARCH_HINTS section with specific paths/keywords for the researcher stage\n5. Set the PRD Status to \"READY\" if all required fields are complete\n\nDo NOT ask the user questions - the answers are already provided. Focus on synthesizing the PRD content based on the given answers.","a